- It's all waxed up.
- All waxed up? What do you mean?

18:02.815 --> 18:05.807
- I need something. Ajob for my dad.
- Yeah, yeah. Sure. Okay.

18:05.918 --> 18:09.285
Listen to me.
Brand new cars don't get waxed!

18:09.388 --> 18:11.856
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>That afternoon it was game time...</i>

18:11.957 --> 18:14.448
<i>and Michael felt confident</i>
<i>about a Bluth win.</i>

18:16.962 --> 18:19.192
Spin, spin, spin.

18:19.298 --> 18:24.031
<i>[Narrator] Ann wasn't as amazing as</i>
<i>George Michael led his father to believe.</i>

18:25.104 --> 18:27.299
<i>But Gob was playing</i>
<i>worse than ever...</i>

18:27.406 --> 18:30.307
<i>as per his agreement with Michael.</i>

18:37.749 --> 18:41.082
<i>Your guy can't hit, Sitwell.</i>
<i>He's never gonna touch it.</i>

18:41.186 --> 18:43.245
- Time out.
- Time out.

18:43.355 --> 18:45.482
Gob, are you okay?

18:45.591 --> 18:48.389
Yeah, just can't hit today.
Guess you're really disappointed in me.

18:48.494 --> 18:51.657
Hey. Everybody has days like this.
It's only a game.

18:51.763 --> 18:54.823
After that list of ideas you gave me,
I don't care if you blow the whole season.

18:54.933 --> 18:57.663
Come here, you.

18:59.071 --> 19:00.834
Okay. We're good.

19:00.939 --> 19:04.898
<i>[Narrator] And Gob finally felt</i>
<i>that someone believed in him.</i>

19:05.010 --> 19:08.673
<i>Even though they weren't his ideas.</i>

19:08.780 --> 19:11.408
<i>And he decided</i>
<i>to make Sitwell proud.</i>

19:14.553 --> 19:16.680
<i>[Michael]</i>
<i>Get on that ball!</i>

19:19.024 --> 19:21.515
You go!

19:21.627 --> 19:23.527
You better pull an ankle or something.

19:23.629 --> 19:25.529
<i>Come on, George Michael!</i>
<i>Get that ball in there!</i>

19:25.631 --> 19:27.690
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Then he went headfirst into The Wall.</i>

19:27.799 --> 19:29.767
- I'm safe.
- You're out!

19:29.868 --> 19:33.201
<i>Out? I was safe! I'm safe!</i>

19:33.305 --> 19:36.365
- Stop with the Tweety Bird dance, you moron.
- Dad?

19:36.475 --> 19:38.807
He made the call. You're out.
What are you doing?

19:38.911 --> 19:40.708
- Shush, shush, shush.
- Dad?

19:40.812 --> 19:43.212
- He's safe.
- What the hell are you doing here?

19:43.315 --> 19:46.409
I'm taking care of what you
screwed up. You blew it again, Michael.

19:46.518 --> 19:50.887
Let me tell you something. I blew it when
I let you start controlling me again.

19:50.989 --> 19:52.889
I even stooped to cheat here
at a softball game.

19:52.991 --> 19:55.391
You've been talking to each other.
How come nobody called me?

19:55.494 --> 19:58.793
- What's going on there?
- I'm just fixing something that's been bugging me.

19:58.897 --> 20:01.491
- <i>He was safe.</i>
- [Cheering]

20:01.600 --> 20:05.229
He was. We lost.
Get over it.

20:05.337 --> 20:08.829
Yeah, and Stan Sitwell liked my ideas.
He really believed in me.

20:08.941 --> 20:10.738
- My ideas.
- Well.

20:10.842 --> 20:13.743
And I'm president, whether
you like it or not, Dad.

20:13.845 --> 20:15.972
I don't need your approval anymore.

20:17.549 --> 20:20.848
- I'm proud of you.
- Really?

20:20.953 --> 20:23.046
Yeah. See ya.

20:26.058 --> 20:28.583
Michael, I could've sworn
I just saw Dad.

20:28.694 --> 20:32.095
Or not. I think hallucination
is one of the side-effects ofTeamocil.

20:32.197 --> 20:34.324
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>It isn't.</i>

20:34.433 --> 20:36.731
- Thanks for making the right call there, Mike.
- Yeah.

20:36.835 --> 20:39.963
- Sorry I didn't blow the game.
- No. You did the right thing...

20:40.072 --> 20:42.632
and you finally got Dad
to one of your ball games.

20:42.741 --> 20:45.369
- Screw him.
- Yeah.

20:45.477 --> 20:49.140
[Whistling Through Teeth]
I miss him so much.

20:49.248 --> 20:52.012
